                    <span>This book is a must read for anyone who wants to be anyone in marketing.  As a student, I have found Brand Leadership to be a valuable tool.  It has really built on a totally new dimension to marketing that I haven't encountered in any strategy or marketing class.  Aaker and Joachimsthaler break new ground with their Brand Leadership Model by moving away from the static, short-term traditional marketing and communication models that focus on TV and advertising and don't take into account the vital role the brand plays in an organization's strength, let alone the value that it brings to a company's balance sheet.  This book introduces an entirely new perspective on marketing as it encompasses brand-building with strategy, leadership and change.  Make sure you read "Part IV: Building Brands Beyond Advertising" to get a new stance on brand-building methods.  Read it, you'll never look back!</span>
                  
